<collectingCountry id="F3667631819BFF37FE62F97BFDFEF937" box="[494,589,1739,1765]" name="Vietnam" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and southwestern and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3667631819BFF37FC39F97BFC4FF937" box="[949,1020,1739,1765]" name="China" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE36A1819BFF37FF31F940FAE0F833" blockId="180.[136,1452,1631,2018]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FF31F940FE95F8D8" bold="true" box="[189,294,1776,1802]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Notes:—</emphasis>
The first 
<specimenCount id="9D77FD28819BFF37FE05F940FD9DF8DB" box="[393,558,1775,1802]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
cited above are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FCC3F940FC40F8DB" box="[847,1011,1776,1801]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Panisea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FCC3F940FC40F8DB" box="[847,1011,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">P. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differ in the weakly clawed oblonglanceolate lip (the 
<typeStatus id="54CA8803819BFF37FEDAF8A4FE35F8FC" box="[342,390,1812,1838]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FE26F8A4FDFCF8FF" box="[426,591,1812,1837]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Panisea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FE26F8A4FDFCF8FF" box="[426,591,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">P. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an oblong-spathulate lip that is prominently clawed). It could here not be ascertained whether they fall into the range of variation of this species, and further work is currently being undertaken. 
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FF04F8EBFECFF8A4" box="[136,380,1883,1910]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Kingdon-Ward 10144</emphasis>
(BM) has previously been identified as possibly belonging to the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FAA0F8EBFF62F84B" authority="Schltr." authorityName="Schltr." class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ischnogyne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FAA0F8EBFA1FF8A7" box="[1324,1452,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Ischnogyne</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
by E.F. de Vogel. The only currently known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FCDBF8CFFC64F84B" box="[855,983,1919,1945]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ischnogyne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FCDBF8CFFC64F84B" box="[855,983,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Ischnogyne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FC6BF830FACAF84B" authority="(Kraenzl.) Schltr." authorityName="Schltr." baseAuthorityName="Kraenzl." box="[999,1401,1919,1946]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ischnogyne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mandarinorum">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FC6BF830FB1AF84B" box="[999,1193,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">I. mandarinorum</emphasis>
(Kraenzl.) Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
, has flowers three times larger than those of 
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FDC9F814FD7EF86C" box="[581,717,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<accessionNumber id="9422AB42819BFF37FDC9F814FD7EF86C" box="[581,717,1956,1982]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/FKW10144" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">FKW 10144</accessionNumber>
</emphasis>
and is currently considered endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3667631819BFF37FB00F813FB60F86F" box="[1164,1235,1955,1981]" name="China" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">China</collectingCountry>
. Generally, it is not clear whether 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FEABF877FE14F833" box="[295,423,1991,2017]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Ischnogyne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FEABF877FE14F833" box="[295,423,1991,2017]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Ischnogyne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nested in 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D22819BFF37FDBEF878FD3FF833" box="[562,652,1992,2017]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Panisea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B905EAB3819BFF37FDBEF878FD3FF833" box="[562,652,1992,2017]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Panisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has apparently not yet benefitted from DNA studies.
</paragraph>
